<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-5133] TCompactProtocol string allocation improvement</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5133</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;WriteStringAsync &amp;amp;&#160;ReadStringAsync in&#160;TCompactProtocol each allocate a buffer to store UTF8 bytes when converting to and from strings. This buffer has to be cleaned up by the garbage collector (at some point), which can lead to a lot of pressure on the hosting process in high-volume scenarios. Basically a lot of short-lived buffers are being emitted by the library. It&apos;s an easy tweak to use a pooled buffer for this work which greatly improves the performance under load.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
